title: Grateful Dead Live at Soldier Field on 1992-06-26
description: Hell In A Bucket, Peggy-O, The Same Thing, Loose Lucy, Mexicali Blues-> Maggie's Farm, Tennessee Jed, Picasso Moon Corinna-> Crazy Fingers-> Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums, Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Wharf Rat, Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: The Weight

reviews.review_text:
solid show we were 20 rows back in front of Phil this night. while this show is often overshadowed by the night before this is a solid summer 92 show.
the sound dynamic this night was fabulous for a huge stadium show. there were not any standout performnaces per se, but in my opinion the entire show from start to finish rocked...with an especially great wharf rat.
Does anyone have a copy of this show? This was an amazing show and one of my friend's first Dead show.  If anyone has a copy of this show, I'd appreciate it!

my one and only good show not outstanding but good ol' grateful dead show 

great guitar at the end of crazy fingers great drums AND I LOVED TO CLAPPIN MY HANDS WITH 80 000 PEOPLE ON NFA

thank you Jerry thank you Giuseppe

Chicago rules !!!!

Must say this 92 summer tour rocked the weather was impeccable and these chi town shows were so much fun.The Grateful Dead is playing well and is gelling nicely with vince. Often people try to compare the keyboardists but i think it is clear they all brought different sounds to the Dead. I like them all. Put that in your pipe and smoke it and you know, being from Toronto We have all BC buds we need.

Frosty's Picks for the Hearing Impaired I have major hearing problems. It’s called tinnitus and for those of you who don’t know it is a constant ringing in your ears. Therefore, it is hard for me to find audience shows that are of good enough quality for me to listen to without doing further damage to my hearing (by having to turn up the volume past 5 to even tell what song is being played!).  I am not saying anything about these shows except that as a person with major hearing lose, these are some of the shows that I have on my I-Pod.  Of course some are better than others. However, I am not giving any of these shows a review. I can always find something good in every show…...as long as I can hear it!!!! Here is my list for today, 9/20/08:

7.6.84,         10.15.84,      6.19.91,    
7.18.89,        6.21.84,       9.6.85,

Pretty Good Show ! Soldier Field,  I do not like to judge or rate shows, other than it was a pretty good show. What made it special was that I took my son with to the Show. It was the occassion of his 13th birthday. As I spread the word around me, folks were yelling "happy Birthday" to him.  What a way to become a teenager.  He hop[ed the boys wopuld play Not Fade Away cause he likes the bop, bop audience participation and the heavy drumming style. Well son,  if all the stars and planets are lined up just right maybe, just maybe.... So there is came right near the end, and what a fantastic fireworks diaplay.

4th Show Overall scene was tripical of Soldier Field. #1 Crazy Fingers of the 90's. Dark and melodic as no-one else can.
Give it a listen!
